tspan.tspan: Alex
Alex is a hunter for the Noka
, used to travelling far and
wide throughout the subterranean depths - trading goods,
sourcing food and clothing, and defending the camp from
rogues and servo robots. Theyre currently on
reconnaissance, but are long overdue. Theyve had
problems with alcohol in the past; how will they feel when
they learn about you - someone who is faster and stronger,
and can do their job better than they can?
Jack
Jack is chief engineer of the Noka
, in charge of maintaining
their makeshift habitats among the ruined skyscrapers, and
the irrigation that waters their crops. Truth be told,
Catherine does most of the hard work, which shes happy to
do since Jack's prosthetic leg seriously hinders his
mobility.
Though even if he was able, its unlikely Jack
would get his
hands dirty - hes selfish, grumpy, and
distrustful, especially
of you.
Catherine
Catherine is the one who found you
and brought you back
online. Shes young and spontaneous, and the best engineer
the Noka have. Her fascination with technology and knack
for fixing things means she really appreciates you as an
android. Shes also young enough not to buy into the scare
stories about androids, and is the one to first give you a
proper name.
Fi
Fi is chieftain of the Noka
, the small faction that found you
in the rubble. Theyre trying to eke out a life by farming on
the barren surface. She's quiet and considerate, but
responsibility weighs heavy on her mind, after she led her
friends away from the militaristic and monopolising Wraw
faction, deep underground. Although distrustful of your
intentions, she nevertheless sees you as an asset. But will
she ever warm to you as a person?
The Stranger
Your character.
You were a detective-model android before
the calamity, but you can barely remember any of that - not
even your name. All you know is that nearly thirty
years
have passed since you were last active. Your systems
are
mostly intact: you are fast, strong, and possess both
keen
observational skills and an Artemis sword at your side.
You
will be in demand, but you may strike fear into those
you
meet. After all, your capabilities also present a danger.
